rComments: Very boring class. The material is dry. Multiple choice questions are ridiculous. The final exam was also ridiculous. Overall an extremly boring class with hard tests and exams

If you are not in this program, it is not worth your time. The class doesn't flow entirely and you will fall asleep unless you are really interested in rocks and all of that stuff.  The course description highly misleading.

Very good professor. I actually found the material taught quite interesting with the way he taught. He explains all the concepts very well. Really glad he changed the tests to have written answers too. I also wouldn't recommend getting the textbook, his notes are good enough to study off of.

Great professor, show knowledge, and enthusiasm in his own field. Its geology, and obviously not everyone will be interested, but his explains it in an understandable manner. Not a whole lot of textbook use

Great prof. Super helpful, explains everything, answers all questions during class. The class I had was from 5:30 to 8:30, so it's obviously difficult to keep the material interesting but I was interested enough that I didn't check the clock at all.
